-- RBS’s Sabatini Leaves, Structured Products Magazine Reports
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   M a r s h
-- 2012-05-01T15:51:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/rbs-s-sabatini-leaves-structured-products-magazine-reports.html
Andrea Sozzi Sabatini left  Royal Bank
of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  as head of European and Latin American
equity derivatives and structured-note sales, Structured
Products magazine reported.  Sabatini was based in  London  where he reported to Beat von Gunten, the global head of sales for equities and structured
retail products, the magazine said, citing people familiar with
the matter that it didn’t identify. He joined RBS with the
takeover of ABN Amro Bank NV in 2007.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alastair Marsh in London at 
 amarsh25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Armstrong at 
 parmstrong10@bloomberg.net  